insert into public.knowledge_snapshots (source_key, content_hash, fetched_at, from_cache, bytes, text_chars, document_path, extract, metadata) values ('jp-customs-origin-verification', 'f71d5cb09fa4ed1dd99dfbc76372570dd98336c45a56e754d48de040f9110d4c', '2026-06-25T09:45:50.145Z', true, 27618, 5530, 'data/knowledge/documents/jp-customs-origin-verification.md', 'ORIGIN VERIFICATION : Japan Customs Skip to Content Menu Home Passenger Export / Import Enforcement Trade Statistics Customs Answer(FAQ) Regional Customs Hakodate Tokyo Yokohama Nagoya Osaka Kobe Moji Nagasaki Okinawa Site Map Japanese Site Map Japanese Location: Rules of Origin > ORIGIN VERIFICATION ORIGIN VERIFICATION *There are links to PDF files below. (1) Purpose of verification &ldquo;Verification&rdquo; is a process of confirming the originating status of goods which have already been imported under preferential tariff treatment of Economic Partnership Agreements (EPAs) or Generalized System of Preferences (GSP). Customs conducts verification of origin in accordance with the provision of each EPA and Customs-related laws and regulations. In order to benefit from the preferential tariff under an EPA or GSP, the imported good must qualify as originating in accordance with the applicable rules of origin of the EPA or GSP. Through verification, Customs ensures the proper application of preferential tariff treatment under EPAs or GSP. (2) Methods of verification As for the verification with the importer, Customs sends a written request for information on the originating status of the imported good(s). Customs determines whether the good qualifies as originating on the basis of the information and documents provided by the importer. If the originating status of the good is not confirmed through the verification with the importer, Customs may carry out verification with the exporter or producer. Customs sends a written request for information to the exporter or producer, or conducts a verification visit to the premises (e.g. factories or offices) of the exporter or producer. If Customs cannot confirm the originating status of the good through the above process, preferential tariff treatment would be denied. Furthermore, depending on the cases, the good may be subject to an additional tax/penalties for underpayment of Customs duties. (Download Files) Form - REQUEST FOR INFORMATION ON THE ORIGIN OF GOODS Japan Customs sends this form to request information regarding the originating status of the imported goods. This form may be sent to the exporter, producer or the competent authority of the exporting party of an EPA or a GSP beneficiary country, depending on the preferential duty rate claimed by the importer. The addressee of this form is requested to promptly fill out and send back the form to Japan Customs. Reference &#12539;Application of Rules of Origin (ROO) of Japan-EU EPA and Japan-UK EPA to the used product (3) Cases of origin irregularities related to EPA or GSP The followings are reference cases for importers regarding products that were declared for import under the preferential tariff rates under EPA or GSP, but that were found to be NOT originating and not eligible for the preferential tariff rates, through origin verification process by Japan Customs. These cases are published for the purpose of ensuring compliance by importers further, who are required to confirm by themselves whether the products satisfy the rules of origin, even if they have obtained a Certification of Origin issued by the exporting country. Please make the most use of this information. *How to view the cases. Reference cases No. HS code Product EPA/GSP 1 HS 03.03 Fish CPTPP 2 HS 03.06 Frozen shrimps (Head) RCEP (from China) 3 HS 03.07 Salted jellyfishes Japan-Thailand EPA 4 HS 06.04 Dried plants for ornamental purposes Japan-India Comprehensive Partnership Agreement (JICEPA) 5 HS 07.11 Salted vegetables Japan-EU EPA 6 HS 09.01 Coffee beans Japan-Australia EPA 7 HS 1604.14 Preparations of tuna Japan-Thailand EPA 8 HS 1604.15 Preparations of mackerel Japan-ASEAN EPA (from Thailand) 9 HS 1605.20 Deep-fried shrimp cutlets Japan-Thailand EPA 10 HS 17.04 Candies Japan-EU EPA 11 HS 18.05 Cocoa powder Japan-Indonesia EPA 12 HS 19.02 Pasta Japan-EU EPA 13 HS 19.05 Cookies Generalized System of Preferences (GSP) 14 HS 19.05 Snacks Generalized System of Preferences (GSP) 15 HS 19.05 Bakers&rsquo; wares Japan-Indonesia EPA 16 HS 2005.20 Preparations of potatoes Japan-Malaysia EPA 17 HS 20.06 Fruit preserved by sugar Japan-Thailand EPA 18 HS 2008.92 Preparations of fruit (mixtures) Japan-Philippines EPA 19 HS 2009.41 Pineapple juice Japan-EU EPA 20 HS 2009.90 Mixtures of juices Japan-Thailand EPA 21 HS 22.04 Wine Japan-EU EPA 22 HS 2710.19 Lubricant Japan-Thailand EPA 23 HS 2924.29 Pigment intermediate Japan-India Comprehensive Partnership Agreement (JICEPA) 24 HS 2933.69 Agrichemical product Japan-India Comprehensive Partnership Agreement (JICEPA) 25 HS 57.02 Floor coverings Generalized System of Preferences (GSP) 26 HS 57.02 Floor coverings Japan-EU EPA 27 HS 61.10 Articles of apparel, knitted or crocheted Japan-EU EPA 28 HS 62.01 Articles of apparel, not knitted or crocheted CPTPP 29 HS 62.11 Articles of apparel, not knitted or crocheted Japan-ASEAN EPA (from Viet Nam) 30 HS 63.02 Towel Generalized System of Preferences (GSP) 31 HS 63.07 Knitted article Japan-EU EPA About Us Organization Central Customs Laboratory Customs Trainig Institute Regional Customs Jurisdiction and Location Laws,Policy Related Laws Outline of Amendment WTO FTA / EPA CMAA Procedure and Form Customs Procedure Customs Form Other Information Brochure Report PR activities of the Customs Japan Customs X guide line Top of Page Top of Page Notice Privacy Policy Inquiry Customs and Tariff Bureau, 3-1-1 Kasumigaseki, Chiyoda-ku, Tokyo 100-8940, JAPAN Copyright(C) Ministry of Finance Japan', '{"source_registry_version":"2026-06-25","authority":"Japan Customs","domain":"origin_labeling","tags":["origin","fta","verification","customs"],"format":"html","page_count":null,"parse_error":null}'::jsonb) on conflict (source_key, content_hash) do update set fetched_at = excluded.fetched_at, from_cache = excluded.from_cache, bytes = excluded.bytes, text_chars = excluded.text_chars, document_path = excluded.document_path, extract = excluded.extract, metadata = excluded.metadata;
